AIM -> To create a class in Python and demonstrate object creation and methods to calculate total marks.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Define a class named Student.
Initialize name, USN and marks using input.
Create a method to calculate total marks.
Display total marks along with student details.
Create an object of the class.
Call the method using the object.
Stop the program.

SOURCE CODE:

class Student:
    name = "Arpit"
    age = 20
    address = "Bangalore"

details = Student()

print("Name is", details.name)
print("Age is", details.age)
print("Address is", details.address)


class student:

    def __init__(self):
        self.name = input("Enter the name:")
        self.usn = input("Enter the USN:")
        self.marks1 = int(input("Enter the marks1:"))
        self.marks2 = int(input("Enter the marks2:"))
        self.marks3 = int(input("Enter the marks3:"))

    def total_marks(self):
        print("Total marks:", self.marks1 + self.marks2 + self.marks3)
        print("Name:", self.name)
        print("USN:", self.usn)


obj = student()
obj.total_marks()
